article.headline: Dant, by dint of 27 points, leads DePaul
article.linkText: DePaul solidifies C-USA lead in OT vs. TCU
article.story:
CHICAGO (AP) -- Jenni Dant scored 27 points, and No. 15 DePaul
beat TCU 84-81 in overtime Sunday.

Khara Smith and Jenna Rubino added 14 points apiece to help the
Blue Demons (21-3, 10-1 Conference USA) win their 10th straight and
22nd consecutive at home. Smith also had 14 rebounds.

Sandora Irvin led TCU (17-8, 8-3) with 25 points. She also
pulled down a game-high 18 rebounds. Niki Newton scored 15 points,
Ashley Davis scored 13 points, and Natasha Lacy and Lorie
Butler-Rayford added 12 points each. Lacy also had a game-high 11
assists.

DePaul, which grabbed the top spot in the conference on Friday
when they beat Houston and TCU lost to Marquette, was 15-of-23 from
the free throw line. TCU hit just four of 15 shots from the line.

Dant went 7-for-13 from the field, including 4-for-5 on
3-pointers.

DePaul led 38-35 at halftime, but TCU outscored DePaul 39-36 to
send the game to overtime. DePaul outscored TCU 10-7 in overtime.
